        "title": "fix(gateway): regenerate native hook descriptors when relay unavailable after restart",
        "body": "## Problem\nNative hook relay descriptors could become stale after gateway restart when the Codex app-server relay was unavailable. Fallback to RPC was not attempted.\n\n## Fix\nFall through to gateway RPC when native hook direct-bridge errors occur. Regenerate descriptors on relay failure instead of returning stale state.\n\n## Changes\n- `extensions/codex/src/app-server/approval-bridge.ts` (+5 -7)\n- `extensions/codex/src/app-server/approval-bridge.test.ts` (+7 -9)\n- `src/cli/native-hook-relay-cli.ts` (+5 -2)\n- `src/cli/native-hook-relay-cli.test.ts` (+16 -27)\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8)\n```\n✓ src/cli/native-hook-relay-cli.test.ts (20 tests, 100% pass)\n```\n\n### Behavior addressed\nNative hook relay now regenerates descriptors on failure and falls back to gateway RPC.\n\n### Evidence after fix\nAll 20 native hook relay CLI tests pass.",
